## Verification Plan

### Automated
```bash
# Backend starts clean
cd backend && python3 -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload

# Health endpoint
curl http://localhost:8000/health

# SSE sync endpoint (requires GitHub token or public repo)
curl -N -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/github/sync \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"repo": "facebook/react"}' 
# Should stream cluster_found events
```

### Manual
1. Land on `/` → click "Sign in with GitHub" → auto-advances to `/select-repo`
2. Type `facebook/react` and hover sync button (connection warms)
3. Click → navigate to `/dashboard`
4. Watch cluster cards stream in live as DBSCAN identifies topological boundaries
